Implemented Vercel Speed Insights for Next.js Application

## Changes Made:

### 1. Package Installation
- Installed `@vercel/speed-insights` version 2.0.0 using pnpm
- Updated package.json with the new dependency

### 2. Configuration
Modified `/app/layout.tsx`:
- Added import: `import { SpeedInsights } from "@vercel/speed-insights/next";`
- Added `<SpeedInsights />` component to the root layout within the body element, following Next.js App Router best practices

### 3. Files Modified:
- `app/layout.tsx` - Added SpeedInsights component to root layout
- `package.json` - Added @vercel/speed-insights dependency
- `pnpm-lock.yaml` - Updated lock file with new dependencies

### 4. Verification:
- Build completed successfully with no errors
- The SpeedInsights component is now integrated and will track page performance metrics
- Placed after the existing Analytics component to maintain proper initialization order

## Implementation Details:

Following the official Vercel Speed Insights quickstart documentation (fetched from https://vercel.com/docs/speed-insights/quickstart), the implementation:
- Uses the Next.js-specific import path `@vercel/speed-insights/next`
- Places the component within the body element of the root layout for proper tracking across all pages
- Requires no additional props for basic functionality
- Will automatically collect and send performance metrics once the site is deployed to Vercel

## Next Steps:

To fully enable Speed Insights:
1. Deploy the application to Vercel
2. Navigate to the Speed Insights section in the Vercel dashboard
3. Click the "Enable" button to activate Speed Insights for this project

The implementation is complete and ready for deployment.
